Get up, get out, go home,

01:11.642 --> 01:13.777
apologize to Adrian
and go to school!

01:16.047 --> 01:17.080
Now!

01:29.794 --> 01:34.564
Wouldn't it be great if the past three
years just turned out to be a dream

01:34.599 --> 01:35.966
and today's the first
day of high school?

01:37.034 --> 01:38.602
Yeah.

01:53.050 --> 01:54.684
Good morning.

01:56.754 --> 01:58.021
You already showered?

01:58.055 --> 01:59.923
I was hoping we
could shower together.

01:59.957 --> 02:02.759
This house is having a crazy
effect on you, you know that?

02:02.794 --> 02:04.728
Is it?

02:04.762 --> 02:05.862
It must be
all the space.

02:05.897 --> 02:07.531
Maybe.

02:07.565 --> 02:08.931
But we better not
get used to that.

02:08.966 --> 02:10.699
We better get used
to no space

02:10.735 --> 02:12.869
and sleeping on our new
couch in the living room.

02:12.904 --> 02:14.738
I can't wait to see it.

02:14.772 --> 02:16.673
I can't wait
to sleep on it.

02:16.707 --> 02:17.808
With you.

02:20.912 --> 02:23.680
Hmm. John fell
back asleep.

02:23.714 --> 02:24.915
He was tired
this morning.

02:24.949 --> 02:26.783
I'm not.

02:26.818 --> 02:30.720
Come on,
we have to get going.

02:31.989 --> 02:33.557
We have to get to school.

02:33.591 --> 02:34.825
And you have
that interview today.

02:34.859 --> 02:36.626
We've got
plenty of time.

02:36.661 --> 02:38.562
I'm not worried
about the interview.

02:38.596 --> 02:40.297
Either they let me in to
that school or they don't.

02:40.331 --> 02:43.600
If they don't, then you're going to be
away at school while John and I are here.

02:43.634 --> 02:45.035
I'll drive back
and forth every day.

02:45.069 --> 02:46.703
You can't do that.

02:46.737 --> 02:48.672
I can do anything
I have to do.

02:48.706 --> 02:50.607
Okay, well, then you have
to ace that interview

02:50.641 --> 02:52.609
because it's really too late
to apply anywhere else.

02:52.643 --> 02:54.811
So, come on,
let's get going.

02:54.846 --> 02:56.746
We have to get John fed before
he goes to the nursery.

02:56.781 --> 02:59.583
And you still have to stop by the
apartment to get your books and things.

02:59.617 --> 03:01.618
My books and things
are in the car.

03:01.652 --> 03:03.887
I actually thought I might get
some studying done last night.

03:03.921 --> 03:05.589
But you didn't.

03:05.623 --> 03:06.790
No, I didn't.

03:06.824 --> 03:08.992
And yet, I still managed to
learn a little something.

03:09.026 --> 03:11.595
Stop!

03:12.830 --> 03:15.832
You're making me blush.

03:15.867 --> 03:19.536
Are you sure we can't have just a
few more minutes to ourselves?

03:19.570 --> 03:20.604
I'm sure.

03:24.642 --> 03:25.842
I love you, Amy.

03:26.777 --> 03:28.745
I love you, too, Ricky.

03:35.753 --> 03:47.964
Adrian?

03:47.999 --> 03:49.599
Adrian?

04:00.545 --> 04:01.578
Adrian!

04:03.614 --> 04:04.714
Great.

